## -------
## Go build / test artifacts
## Go has no standard build-output directory (binaries land in the current dir or
## wherever `go build -o` points), so this ignores the usual loose outputs.
## -------
# Compiled binaries / plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
# Test binary built with `go test -c`
*.test
# Output of `go tool cover` and profiling
*.out
coverage.*
# Go workspace files (per-developer; not committed)
go.work
go.work.sum
# Vendored dependencies (uncomment if you do NOT commit `go mod vendor` output)
# /vendor/

## -------
## Editors / IDEs
## -------
.vs/
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
*.code-workspace
.history/
.idea/

## -------
## Secrets / local config
## -------
.env
.env.local

## -------
## macOS
## -------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

## -------
## Windows
## -------
Thumbs.db
Thumbs.db:encryptable
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
*.lnk

## -------
## Claude Code — ship the shared settings with the repo, even if a global
## gitignore excludes .claude. Personal overrides stay ignored.
## -------
!.claude/
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/settings.json.template
.claude/settings.local.json

## -------
## Agent-local guidance — present on disk for tooling, never pushed.
## `.claude/` here overrides the ship-negations above (a later dir-exclude wins).
## -------
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/CLAUDE.local.md
.claude/
